Security and medical personnel seen outside the Maserati dealership in Bryanston. Image by: Medi Response via Twitter Armed robbers struck at a Maserati dealership in Johannesburg north on Saturday morning taking two hostages and a vehicle on Saturday morning. The hostages employees at the dealership in William Nicol Drive in Bryanston were later released unharmed by the robbers. Police spokesperson Lieutenant Kay Makhubela said that at around 11am five armed men cornered two drivers who were about to leave the dealership to fill two cars with fuel . Makhubela said the armed robbers forced the drivers to lie down in the back of a white Maserati Levante and the vehicle was taken from the dealership. The other car was left at the dealership but Makhubela said that keys to other vehicles were taken during the robbery. The drivers were dropped off in a field in Bassonia south of Johannesburg and were unharmed Makhubela said. Managing director of Medi-Response Hadley Shapiro said that his rescue service was called to the scene at approximately 11am and that both drivers were unharmed. Police are on the lookout for the white Maserati Levante and have appealed to the public to come forward with any information about the robbery. A message circulating on social media and purported to have been released by Maserati said that the vehicle had been recovered. #Update #Maserati PR disaster #BOLO After initially asking everyone to not name the brand of vehicle stolen they are now saying thanks pic.twitter.com/AICz274jd1 &mdash; Trending Crimes SA (@CICArsa) March 25, 2017 Makhubela however said that he had not received any information about the vehicle having been recovered and that police were still on the lookout for the Maserati. Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share